videos.headline: New Mexico State strikes first as McQuarley finds the end zone
videos.description: Richard McQuarley runs it up the gut to score from three yards out, giving the Lobos an early 7-0 lead.

videos.headline: Owens turns on the jets to get Lobos into Rams' territory
videos.description: Tyrone Owens rips off a huge 54-yard run, getting New Mexico State all the way down to the Colorado State 30-yard line.

videos.headline: Colorado State's Fackrell makes contested grab, holds on with one hand
videos.description: Dalton Fackrell jumps up to reel in a pass over a defender and maintains possession as he's falling to the ground by holding the ball above his head.

videos.headline: Rams' Stevens fools defense with pump fake, finds Fackrell for TD
videos.description: QB Nick Stevens gets the defense to bite on a pass fake and then connects with a wide-open Dalton Fackrell in the end zone for a seven-yard touchdown, tying the game at 7-7.

videos.headline: Johnson wins jump ball in end zone for Colorado State TD
videos.description: Nick Stevens throws a fade into the end zone and Olabisi Johnson skies above the defender to haul in the pass for a 14-yard touchdown, putting the Rams ahead 14-7.

videos.headline: Rams' Matthews leaps into end zone for TD
videos.description: Izzy Matthews takes a handoff and jumps over the line to score from one yard out, giving Colorado State a 21-10 lead just before halftime.

videos.headline: Bobo feeling confident going into halftime
videos.description: Colorado State coach Mike Bobo says he likes how his team finished the half, scoring a touchdown with under a minute remaining to go into halftime with a 21-10 lead.

videos.headline: Owens eludes defense at line of scrimmage, breaks free for Lobos TD
videos.description: Tyrone Owens jukes two Colorado State defenders at the line and then finds open field, scoring a 25-yard touchdown.

videos.headline: Dropped pass costs Colorado State a touchdown
videos.description: Nick Stevens throws a great pass right into the chest of Warren Jackson, but Jackson can't hold on to the ball in the end zone, forcing the Rams to settle for a field goal.

videos.headline: Rams recover Lobos' fumble
videos.description: New Mexico State RB Richard McQuarley has the ball knocked out of his hands by Shun Johnson and Colorado State's Jakob Buys recovers to force the turnover.

videos.headline: New Mexico's Molina makes contested catch in end zone
videos.description: On fourth-and-goal with under a minute remaining, Tevaka Tuioti goes to the end zone and connects with Aaron Molina for a 12-yard touchdown, cutting Colorado State's lead to three.

videos.headline: Bobo: 'I'm so proud of our guys' after win over New Mexico State
videos.description: Colorado State coach Mike Bobo says his team persevered down the stretch to hold off the Lobos' comeback effort, winning the game 27-24.
